Apple has announced that it is adding a range of new features to tvOS – its operating system for Apple TV. The company will launch a redesigned home screen for the OS which shows full-screen previews. Multi-user support – which allows for multiple user profiles on a single device – will also be added to tvOS. Additionally, support for Apple Music and Apple Arcade will work with tvOS and its multiple user profiles. Good news for gamers is that Apple is also adding support for Xbox One and PlayStation 4 controllers to Apple TV. This will allow for an improved gaming experience.